from earth_data_utils import *
from search_data import *

def search_and_get_sst():
  auth_earthaccess()
  results = earthaccess.search_data(
      short_name=sst_short_name,
      cloud_hosted=True,
      temporal=("2021-07-01", "2021-07-04"),
  )
  print("found results: ", results)
  return results

def search_ssh():
  auth_earthaccess()
  results = earthaccess.search_data(
      short_name=ssh_short_name,
      cloud_hosted=True,
      temporal=("2021-07-01", "2021-09-30"),
  )
  return results

def get_dataset(results):
  return xr.open_mfdataset(earthaccess.open(results))
  
def get_subset(ds):
  return ds['SLA'].sel(Latitude=slice(15.8, 35.9), Longitude=slice(234.5,260.5))
  

def plot_subset(ds_subset):
  ds_subset.std('Time').plot(figsize=(10,6), x='Longitude', y='Latitude')
  home_dir = os.path.expanduser('~')
  
  file_name = f"geoweaver_plot_{str(uuid.uuid4())}.png"
  save_file_path = os.path.join(home_dir, file_name)
  plt.savefig(save_file_path)
  print(f"new figure is saved to {save_file_path}")
  
# plot_subset(get_subset(get_dataset(search_and_get_sst())))
plot_subset(get_subset(get_dataset(search_ssh())))

      short_name=ssh_short_name,
      cloud_hosted=True,
      temporal=("2021-07-01", "2021-09-30"),
  )
  return results

  results = earthaccess.search_data(
      short_name=ssh_short_name,
      cloud_hosted=False,
      temporal=("2021-07-01", "2021-09-30"),
  )
  pprint(results[0])
  ores = earthaccess.open(results)
  print(ores)
  return xr.open_mfdataset(ores)

  return ds['SLA'].sel(Latitude=slice(15.8, 35.9), Longitude=slice(234.5,260.5))

  ds_subset.std('Time').plot(figsize=(10,6), x='Longitude', y='Latitude')
  home_dir = os.path.expanduser('~')
  save_file_path = os.path.join(home_dir, 'plot_subset.png')
  plt.savefig(save_file_path)
  print(f"new figure is saved to {save_file_path}")
  
plot_subset(get_subset(get_dataset()))

      temporal=("2021-07-01", "2021-09-30"),
  )
  return results

  print(f"new figure is saved to {save_file_path}")
  
plot_subset(get_subset(get_dataset()))

    shape=geojson_path,
    temporal={
      'start': dt.datetime(2021, 8, 1, 1),

  results = harmony_client.result_urls(job_id, link_type=LinkType.s3)
  urls = list(results)
  print("urls: ", urls)
  
  url = urls[0]
  print("url: ", url)
  return urls

def get_home_dir():
  home_dir = os.path.expanduser("~")

  results = earthaccess.search_data(

      cloud_hosted=False,
      temporal=("2021-07-01", "2021-09-30"),
  )

def search_and_get_sst():
  sst_short_name="MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1"

  results = earthaccess.search_data(

import os
import requests
import warnings

# Direct access
import earthaccess 
from pprint import pprint
import xarray as xr

# Harmony
import geopandas as gpd
from harmony import BBox, Client, Collection, Request, LinkType
import datetime as dt
import s3fs


auth = earthaccess.login(strategy="netrc")
ssh_short_name = "SEA_SURFACE_HEIGHT_ALT_GRIDS_L4_2SATS_5DAY_6THDEG_V_JPL2205"

results = earthaccess.search_data(
    short_name=ssh_short_name,
    cloud_hosted=True,
    temporal=("2021-07-01", "2021-09-30"),
)
pprint(results[0])
ds = xr.open_mfdataset(earthaccess.open(results))
print(ds)
geojson_url = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/earth-artificial-intelligence/earth_data_cloud_clinic_geoweaver/main/gulf.json'

home_dir = os.path.expanduser('~')
geojson_path = os.path.join(home_dir, 'gulf.json')
response = requests.get(geojson_url)
with open(geojson_path, 'w') as f:
	f.write(response.text)

gdf = gpd.read_file(geojson_path)

harmony_client = Client()
print(geojson_path)
sst_short_name="MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1"

request = Request(
    collection=Collection(id=sst_short_name),
    shape=geojson_path,
    temporal={
    'start': dt.datetime(2021, 8, 1, 1),
    'stop': dt.datetime(2021, 8, 1, 2)   
    },
)

job_id = harmony_client.submit(request)
print(job_id)
harmony_client.wait_for_processing(job_id, show_progress=True)
data = harmony_client.result_json(job_id)
pprint(data)

results = harmony_client.result_urls(job_id, link_type=LinkType.s3)
urls = list(results)
url = urls[0]
print(url)

creds = harmony_client.aws_credentials()
s3_fs = s3fs.S3FileSystem(
    key=creds['aws_access_key_id'],
    secret=creds['aws_secret_access_key'],
    token=creds['aws_session_token'],
    client_kwargs={'region_name':'us-west-2'},
)
f = s3_fs.open(url, mode='rb')
ds = xr.open_dataset(f)

import os
import requests
import warnings

# Direct access
import earthaccess 
from pprint import pprint
import xarray as xr

# Harmony
import geopandas as gpd
from harmony import BBox, Client, Collection, Request, LinkType
import datetime as dt
import s3fs


auth = earthaccess.login(strategy="netrc")
ssh_short_name = "SEA_SURFACE_HEIGHT_ALT_GRIDS_L4_2SATS_5DAY_6THDEG_V_JPL2205"

results = earthaccess.search_data(
    short_name=ssh_short_name,
    cloud_hosted=True,
    temporal=("2021-07-01", "2021-09-30"),
)
pprint(results[0])
ds = xr.open_mfdataset(earthaccess.open(results))
print(ds)
geojson_url = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/earth-artificial-intelligence/earth_data_cloud_clinic_geoweaver/main/gulf.json'

home_dir = os.path.expanduser('~')
geojson_path = os.path.join(home_dir, 'gulf.json')
response = requests.get(geojson_url)
with open(geojson_path, 'w') as f:
	f.write(response.text)

gdf = gpd.read_file(geojson_path)

harmony_client = Client()
print(geojson_path)
sst_short_name="MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1"

request = Request(
    collection=Collection(id=sst_short_name),
    shape=geojson_path,

import os
import requests
from search_data import *
from harmony import BBox, Client, Collection, Request, LinkType
import datetime as dt
import s3fs
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from earth_access_authenticate import *
import earthaccess 
from pprint import pprint
import xarray as xr

# Harmony
import geopandas as gpd

ssh_short_name = "SEA_SURFACE_HEIGHT_ALT_GRIDS_L4_2SATS_5DAY_6THDEG_V_JPL2205"

results = earthaccess.search_data(
    short_name=ssh_short_name,
    cloud_hosted=True,
    temporal=("2021-07-01", "2021-09-30"),
)
sst_short_name="MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1"

results = earthaccess.search_data(
    short_name=ssh_short_name,
    cloud_hosted=True,
    temporal=("2021-07-01", "2021-09-30"),
)

auth = earthaccess.login(strategy="netrc", persist=True)
ds = xr.open_mfdataset(earthaccess.open(results))
geojson_url = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/earth-artificial-intelligence/earth_data_cloud_clinic_geoweaver/main/gulf.json'

home_dir = os.path.expanduser('~')
geojson_path = os.path.join(home_dir, 'gulf.json')
response = requests.get(geojson_url)
with open(geojson_path, 'w') as f:
	f.write(response.text)

gdf = gpd.read_file(geojson_path) #Return a GeoDataFrame object


harmony_client = Client()
sst_short_name="MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1"

request = Request(
  collection=Collection(id=sst_short_name),
  shape=geojson_path,
  temporal={
    'start': dt.datetime(2021, 8, 1, 1),
    'stop': dt.datetime(2021, 8, 1, 2)   
  },
)
job_id = harmony_client.submit(request)
harmony_client.wait_for_processing(job_id, show_progress=False)
data = harmony_client.result_json(job_id)
results = harmony_client.result_urls(job_id, link_type=LinkType.s3)
urls = list(results)
url = urls[0]

creds = harmony_client.aws_credentials()
s3_fs = s3fs.S3FileSystem(
  key=creds['aws_access_key_id'],
  secret=creds['aws_secret_access_key'],
  token=creds['aws_session_token'],
  client_kwargs={'region_name':'us-west-2'},
)
f = s3_fs.open(url, mode='rb')
ds = xr.open_dataset(f)
ds.analysed_sst.plot()
home_dir = os.path.expanduser('~')
plt.savefig(os.path.join(home_dir, 'plot2.png'))

)

results = earthaccess.search_data(

    temporal=("2021-07-01", "2021-09-30"),
)

auth = earthaccess.login(strategy="netrc", persist=True)

)
job_id = harmony_client.submit(request)

sst_short_name="MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1"

results = earthaccess.search_data(
    short_name=ssh_short_name,
    cloud_hosted=True,
    temporal=("2021-07-01", "2021-09-30"),
)

auth = earthaccess.login(strategy="netrc", persist=True)
ds = xr.open_mfdataset(earthaccess.open(results))
geojson_path = '/home/jovyan/gulf.json'
gdf = gpd.read_file(geojson_path) #Return a GeoDataFrame object


harmony_client = Client()
sst_short_name="MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1"

request = Request(
  collection=Collection(id=sst_short_name),
  shape=geojson_path,
  temporal={
    'start': dt.datetime(2021, 8, 1, 1),
    'stop': dt.datetime(2021, 8, 1, 2)   
  },
)
job_id = harmony_client.submit(request)
harmony_client.wait_for_processing(job_id, show_progress=False)
data = harmony_client.result_json(job_id)
results = harmony_client.result_urls(job_id, link_type=LinkType.s3)
urls = list(results)
url = urls[0]

from earth_data_utils import *

ssh_short_name = "SEA_SURFACE_HEIGHT_ALT_GRIDS_L4_2SATS_5DAY_6THDEG_V_JPL2205"

sst_short_name="MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1"

results = earthaccess.search_data(
    short_name=ssh_short_name,
    cloud_hosted=True,
    temporal=("2020-07-01", "2020-09-30"),
)

auth = earthaccess.login(strategy="netrc", persist=True)
ds = xr.open_mfdataset(earthaccess.open(results))
geojson_path = '/home/jovyan/gulf.json'
gdf = gpd.read_file(geojson_path) #Return a GeoDataFrame object


harmony_client = Client()
sst_short_name="MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1"

request = Request(
  collection=Collection(id=sst_short_name),
  shape=geojson_path,
  temporal={
    'start': dt.datetime(2020, 8, 1, 1),
    'stop': dt.datetime(2020, 8, 1, 2)   
  },
)
job_id = harmony_client.submit(request)
harmony_client.wait_for_processing(job_id, show_progress=False)
data = harmony_client.result_json(job_id)
results = harmony_client.result_urls(job_id, link_type=LinkType.s3)
urls = list(results)
url = urls[0]

from earth_data_utils import *

ssh_short_name = "SEA_SURFACE_HEIGHT_ALT_GRIDS_L4_2SATS_5DAY_6THDEG_V_JPL2205"

sst_short_name="MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1"

results = earthaccess.search_data(
    short_name=ssh_short_name,
    cloud_hosted=True,
    temporal=("2020-07-01", "2020-09-30"),
)

auth = earthaccess.login(strategy="netrc", persist=True)
ds = xr.open_mfdataset(earthaccess.open(results))
geojson_path = '/home/jovyan/gulf.json'
gdf = gpd.read_file(geojson_path) #Return a GeoDataFrame object


harmony_client = Client()
sst_short_name="MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1"

request = Request(
  collection=Collection(id=sst_short_name),
  shape=geojson_path,
  temporal={
    'start': dt.datetime(2020, 8, 1, 1),
    'stop': dt.datetime(2020, 8, 1, 2)   
  },
)
job_id = harmony_client.submit(request)
harmony_client.wait_for_processing(job_id, show_progress=False)
data = harmony_client.result_json(job_id)
results = harmony_client.result_urls(job_id, link_type=LinkType.s3)
urls = list(results)
url = urls[0]

from earth_data_utils import *

ssh_short_name = "SEA_SURFACE_HEIGHT_ALT_GRIDS_L4_2SATS_5DAY_6THDEG_V_JPL2205"

sst_short_name="MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1"

results = earthaccess.search_data(
    short_name=ssh_short_name,
    cloud_hosted=True,
    temporal=("2020-07-01", "2020-09-30"),
)

auth = earthaccess.login(strategy="netrc", persist=True)
ds = xr.open_mfdataset(earthaccess.open(results))
geojson_path = '/home/jovyan/gulf.json'
gdf = gpd.read_file(geojson_path) #Return a GeoDataFrame object


harmony_client = Client()
sst_short_name="MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1"

request = Request(
  collection=Collection(id=sst_short_name),
  shape=geojson_path,
  temporal={
    'start': dt.datetime(2020, 8, 1, 1),
    'stop': dt.datetime(2020, 8, 1, 2)   
  },
)
job_id = harmony_client.submit(request)
harmony_client.wait_for_processing(job_id, show_progress=False)
data = harmony_client.result_json(job_id)
results = harmony_client.result_urls(job_id, link_type=LinkType.s3)
urls = list(results)
url = urls[0]

from earth_data_utils import *

ssh_short_name = "SEA_SURFACE_HEIGHT_ALT_GRIDS_L4_2SATS_5DAY_6THDEG_V_JPL2205"

sst_short_name="MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1"

results = earthaccess.search_data(
    short_name=ssh_short_name,
    cloud_hosted=True,
    temporal=("2020-07-01", "2020-09-30"),
)

auth = earthaccess.login(strategy="netrc", persist=True)
ds = xr.open_mfdataset(earthaccess.open(results))
geojson_path = '/home/jovyan/gulf.json'
gdf = gpd.read_file(geojson_path) #Return a GeoDataFrame object


harmony_client = Client()
sst_short_name="MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1"

request = Request(
  collection=Collection(id=sst_short_name),
  shape=geojson_path,
  temporal={
    'start': dt.datetime(2020, 8, 1, 1),
    'stop': dt.datetime(2020, 8, 1, 2)   
  },
)
job_id = harmony_client.submit(request)
harmony_client.wait_for_processing(job_id, show_progress=False)
data = harmony_client.result_json(job_id)
results = harmony_client.result_urls(job_id, link_type=LinkType.s3)
urls = list(results)
url = urls[0]

from earth_data_utils import *

ssh_short_name = "SEA_SURFACE_HEIGHT_ALT_GRIDS_L4_2SATS_5DAY_6THDEG_V_JPL2205"

sst_short_name="MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1"

results = earthaccess.search_data(
    short_name=ssh_short_name,
    cloud_hosted=True,
    temporal=("2020-07-01", "2020-09-30"),
)

auth = earthaccess.login(strategy="netrc", persist=True)
ds = xr.open_mfdataset(earthaccess.open(results))
geojson_path = '/home/jovyan/gulf.json'
gdf = gpd.read_file(geojson_path) #Return a GeoDataFrame object


harmony_client = Client()
sst_short_name="MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1"

request = Request(
  collection=Collection(id=sst_short_name),
  shape=geojson_path,
  temporal={
    'start': dt.datetime(2020, 8, 1, 1),
    'stop': dt.datetime(2020, 8, 1, 2)   
  },
)
job_id = harmony_client.submit(request)
harmony_client.wait_for_processing(job_id, show_progress=False)
data = harmony_client.result_json(job_id)
results = harmony_client.result_urls(job_id, link_type=LinkType.s3)
urls = list(results)
url = urls[0]

ssh_short_name = "SEA_SURFACE_HEIGHT_ALT_GRIDS_L4_2SATS_5DAY_6THDEG_V_JPL2205"

    temporal=("2020-07-01", "2020-09-30"),
)

auth = earthaccess.login(strategy="netrc", persist=True)
ds = xr.open_mfdataset(earthaccess.open(results))
geojson_path = '/home/jovyan/gulf.json'
gdf = gpd.read_file(geojson_path) #Return a GeoDataFrame object

  collection=Collection(id=sst_short_name),
  shape=geojson_path,
  temporal={

)

data = harmony_client.result_json(job_id)

urls = list(results)
url = urls[0]

)

url = urls[0]

)

)

sst_short_name="MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1"

request = Request(
  collection=Collection(id=sst_short_name),
  shape=geojson_path,
  temporal={
    'start': dt.datetime(2021, 8, 1, 1),
    'stop': dt.datetime(2021, 8, 1, 2)   
  },
)
job_id = harmony_client.submit(request)

data = harmony_client.result_json(job_id)
results = harmony_client.result_urls(job_id, link_type=LinkType.s3)
urls = list(results)
url = urls[0]

  results = harmony_client.result_urls(job_id, link_type=LinkType.s3)
  urls = list(results)
  url = urls[0]
except:
  print("please re-run the request")

  print("please re-run the request")

try:
  harmony_client = Client()
  sst_short_name="MUR-JPL-L4-GLOB-v4.1"

  request = Request(
      collection=Collection(id=sst_short_name),
      shape=geojson_path,
      temporal={
      'start': dt.datetime(2021, 8, 1, 1),

  results = harmony_client.result_urls(job_id, link_type=LinkType.s3)
  urls = list(results)
  url = urls[0]
except:
  print("please re-run the request")

)

urls = list(results)
url = urls[0]
